commit.message:
Update cluster-setup.rst

fix typo in readme
Fix to the redis cluster ssl connection.
DOCS: Fix spelling and grammar in pipelining documentation

Fix implementation of CLIENT SETNAME so that it is no longer blocked. Also added note about how to set the connection name by default on all connections newly created. See issue 802 in redis-py. Fixes #327

Create a new more specific error for the cases where a slot is not covered by the cluster. If this happens it will attempt to rebuild the cluster until TTL is expired and then raise that exception back to the user. Fixes #350
Remove accidental pdb in the code
Unblock all stream tests as they all pass and can be run in a clustered env
Rename variable inside execute_command to a better name
Add the python2 compatibility note to the index.rst in docs/ to not only have it in the README file. Minor cleanup and fixes to index file.
Remove Token class checking when use XREADGROUP/XREAD

Implement new feature where remapping the response from "cluster nodes" is now possible to allow for a user to change what ip and port the client thinks the cluster is reachable at. This solves a few use-cases where clients can't connect or figure out how to connect to a cluster after it has reached the initial startup nodes set. Use feature with caution.
Add section about documentation into the contributing document that is presented and used by github
Update release notes with all the changes that has currently been done and is in the code working
Make python 3.5 working again when building and installing this package
Add python2 compatibility note to README
possible fix for the two broken tests that breaks in python 3.8 for unknown reasons
No need to run pytest twice and to kill off the servers as travis will kill it for us at the end of the run anyway
Fix lint and validation warnings/issues in travis.yml file
WIP debugging exception in travis tests
Add empty placeholder files for cluster version of testfiles that might be populated at later time
Add empty placeholder files for cluster versions of testfiles that might be populated at later time
Rename test file
Update test_pubsub.py to upstream version. Block out all tests on the class level instead of having a few open and a few closed inside each class. PubSub is not viable or should be used really.
Fix typo
Update test_pipeline.py to upstream redis-py version. Moved all cluster unique tests and overwrites into test_pipeline_cluster.py
Add block about what to do when a unsupported feature should be blocked off in tests
Update test_multiprocessing.py to be correct from upstream. Fork off all cluster unique tests into test_multiprocessing_cluster.py instead.
Minor cleanup to test_monitor.py to sync with upstream properly
Port in an updated wait for command helper method
Add new text block about testingstrategy and how to write and sync tests from upstream redis-py package going forward.
